@node toascii
@section @code{toascii}---force integers to ASCII range
@findex toascii
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <ctype.h>
int toascii(int @var{c});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
@code{toascii} is a macro which coerces integers to the ASCII range (0--127) by zeroing any higher-order bits.

You can use a compiled subroutine instead of the macro definition by
undefining this macro using `@code{#undef toascii}'.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
@code{toascii} returns integers between 0 and 127.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{toascii} is not ANSI C.

No supporting OS subroutines are required.

@*
